1.What is a Microservice?
    A:- Microservices means breaking your app into multiple small independent services.

2.What is Monolith architecture?
    A:- A monolith is an application where everything is built as one single unit.

3.What is the difference between Monolith and Microservice?
    A:- a.Codebase(Monolith - Single,Microservices - Multiple)
        b.Deployment(Monolith - One,Microservices - Multiple)
        c.Scaling(Monolith - Whole app,Microservices - Individual services)
        d.Complexity(Monolith - Simple,Microservices - Complex)
        e.Speed(start)(Monolith - fast,Microservices - Slower setup)
        f.Maintenance(Monolith - Hard when big,Microservices - Easier when scaled)
        g.Communication(Monolith - Internal,Microservices - APIs(HTTP,queues))

4.Why do we need a useEffect Hook?
    A:-We need useEffect to handle side effects in functional components in a controlled way, ensuring they run at the correct time without causing unnecessary re-renders or performance issues.

5.What is Optional Chaining?
    A:- Optional chaining (?.) is a JavaScript feature that allows safe access to deeply nested object properties without throwing errors if any part is undefined or null.

6.What is Shimmer UI?
    A:- Shimmer UI is a skeleton loading screen(Fake UI while real data loads) with animation that mimics the layout of content, improving user experience while data is being fetched.

7.What is the difference between JS expression and JS statement?
    A:- JS expression produces a value whereas JS statement performs an action(does something --- if,for loop,while,switch,return)

8.What is Conditional Rendering, explain with a code example?
    A:- Conditional Rendering means showing different UI based on some condition.
    AND Operator (&&) -- When you only want to show something if condition is true
    {condition && <Component />}
    function App() {
        const isLoggedIn = true;

        return (
            <div>
            {isLoggedIn ? <h1>Welcome</h1> : <h1>Please Login</h1>}
            </div>
        );
    }
    Output:
    If true = Welcome
    If false = Please Login

9.What is CORS?
    A:- CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a browser mechanism that allows a server to specify which origins are permitted to access its resources, preventing unauthorized cross-origin requests.
    origin means (protocol + Domain + Port)

10.What is async and await?
    A:- async/await is a modern JavaScript feature that allows handling asynchronous operations in a cleaner and more readable way, built on top of Promises.
    Example without async await :
    useEffect(()=>{
        fetch("https://api.com/restaurants")
        .then(res => res.json())
        .then(data => setList(data));
    }, []);

    Example with async await :
    useEffect(()=>{
        async function fetchData() {
            const res = await fetch("https://api.com/restaurants");
            const data = await res.json();
            setList(data)
        }
        fetchData();
    }, []);

11.What is the use of `const json = await data.json();` in getRestaurants()
    A:- .json() reads the response body and converts it into a JavaScript object.



